# Environment files
# .env.local contains real Firebase credentials — DO commit this for Vercel deployment
# .env contains only mock/placeholder values — safe to gitignore
.env
.env.development
.env.production
# NOTE: .env.local is intentionally NOT ignored so Vercel can use the real Firebase config
# If you don't want to commit credentials, add them via: Vercel Dashboard > Project Settings > Environment Variables

